<br>
I'll hold off buying EQ2, none of my friends are buying it either. I'll stick with EQ til something better comes along. I don't trust Sony to make a decent game. The Bean counters may know something, but they don't know how to make a game (see Planetside/SWG). Planetside they tried to use the EQ formula, grind for xp til you get what you want and then have fun with it. The problem was its a FPS not an RPG. Grinding for XP in a FPS is boring. Hence you go into Planetside, you'll see the same amount of servers as was at launch, and the servers being at half or less capacity (friend of mine still plays once in awhile so I get the info from him). And of those playing I wonder how many because of the EQ All Access Pass (since I'm not going to play PS or EQ2 it makes no sense for me). I bet PS population will rocket when EQ2 comes out and people get all access for EQ2 and EQ and get PS with it.<br>
<br>
As for poor service, I didn't encounter many bugs in EQ. Hence I rarely needed EQ CS very much. When I did I did wait exorbiant amounts of time and usually attempted to solve things on my own (CRs in OOT when you get killed by a shark on the boat are joyful. Timourus Deep was even more so &lt;3 Locate Corpse). Planetside wasn't much of a CS game, but you could tell the developers either didn't care or were ordered by the bean counters cause the game was a bore at launch. SWG I got for free as I said, and CS was even worse than EQ. Add to that the game was absolutely full of bugs. Bugs that they knew about in Beta. That shows how little they care about the customer. If you have bugs in beta, fix them before you launch for christ sakes. But no.<br>
<br>
I see EQ2 as being the same as SWG. Sony has enough profit to make a decent game so they actually retain more than 50% of the people after the free month. It shows how little faith they have when they charge shit like $70 for the box (SWG at launch) when they make it all back in subscriptions x10. You sell more at a lower price. Most games are around 50-60 max.<br>
<br>
I see sony as a one hit wonder. They got EQ and from what they've come out with in terms of mmorpgs makes me wary of spending cash on them. I figured I had a hold on PS cause of beta but I was wrong there too. So I say fuck em. They can have my EQ subscription but thats it. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=477296">Kerai</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
